Secure Blogging Platform API
(Multi-User + JWT Auth)

Scenario
Build a backend API for a blogging system with users and posts.

Data Structures
User:
{ id, name, email, passwordHash, role, createdAt }

Post:

{ id, userId, title, content, tags[], createdAt }

Comment:
{ id, postId, userId, comment, createdAt }

Core Tasks
• Register user (bcrypt password hashing)
• Login → generate JWT token
• Middleware to protect routes
• Create / Update / Delete posts
• Add comments to posts
• Get all posts with comments

Logic Challenge
Create getTrendingPosts() based on number of comments

Features
• Role-based access (admin can delete any post)
• Refresh tokens
• Prevent duplicate post titles
• Rate limiting
• Input validation (Joi)